{
 "_name": "s19_singlelayer_multihop_chain",
 "_desc": "Single-layer MULTI-HOP baseline: a redundant 3-hop chain A-{L,L2}-{R,R2}-B with TWO disjoint A<->B paths (no A<->B direct link => every A<->B DM relays >=2 hops). Fills the suite's multi-hop gap (s18/s17 same-layer are single-hop). Doubles as the liveness-reroute base: killing one relay must reroute via the parallel path. Strong lossless links (snr_std_dev 0) so the gate measures HOP COUNT + delivery, not link noise.",
